        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(channels): googlechat auth logging + Zalo mediaMaxBytes default",
        "body": "## What — 2 fixes\n\n### Fix 1: Google Chat webhook auth rejection logging\nSurfaces the auth rejection reason in Google Chat webhook logs when authentication fails (same class of issue as the Telegram crash loop fix in #27454).\n\n### Fix 2: Zalo DEFAULT_MEDIA_MAX_MB 5MB → 20MB\nZalo Official Account files can be up to 20MB. The 5MB default was far below the platform limit and crashes the gateway when users send files in that range.\n\n## Changes\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| extensions/googlechat/src/monitor-webhook.ts | Log verification.reason when auth fails (both auth paths) |\n| extensions/googlechat/src/monitor-types.ts | Add warn to GoogleChatRuntimeEnv type |\n| extensions/zalo/src/monitor.ts | DEFAULT_MEDIA_MAX_MB: 5 → 20 |\n\n11 lines total, 0 deleted. Minimal, surgical, no happy-path impact.\nFixes #57542 (googlechat), Zalo media crash",
